GM NOTES
This questline is designed to:
Replace the "Call of the Greybeards" with Esbern's recruitment
Provide meaningful choices with lasting consequences
Fix Bethesda's mistakes with the Paarthurnax choice
Make the Blades questline feel epic and complete
Respect player agency while maintaining narrative weight
Key Principles:
The choice about Paarthurnax happens BEFORE Alduin so it has mechanical impact
All three outcomes (kill, spare with Blades leaving, spare with Blades convinced) are valid
The "convince Esbern" path is hardest but gives the best outcome
Delphine's fate is tied to the party's earlier betrayal
Esbern is desperate, not evilΓÇöhe genuinely believes he's protecting people
Pacing:
Phase 1-2: 1 session (Esbern contact)
Phase 3: 1 session (Embassy rescue, optional)
Phase 4: 1 session (Sky Haven)
Phase 5-6: 1-2 sessions (Paarthurnax training, Elder Scroll)
