CONCLUSION
This questline replaces the need for a Dragonborn in the world. The party becomes the heroes not because of prophecy, but because of choice, determination, and sacrifice.
The Paarthurnax decision is the moral and narrative climax - not an afterthought, but the defining moment that determines what kind of world Skyrim becomes.
There is no "right" answer. Each choice has consequences. Each path shapes the future.
And in the end, the party must live with what they've chosen.



